Source: gnome-shell-extensions-enhancements
Section: gnome
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Mantas Kriaučiūnas <mantas@baltix.lv>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>=8)
Standards-Version: 3.9.8
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/Baltix/gnome-shell-extensions-enhancements
Homepage: https://launchpad.net/baltix

Package: gnome-shell-extensions-enhancements
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, gnome-shell (>= 3.4), gnome-shell-extension-taskbar, gnome-shell-extension-weather, gnome-shell-extensions
Recommends: gnome-shell-extension-top-icons-plus, gnome-shell-extension-suspend-button, gnome-shell-extensions-gpaste
Suggests: gnome-shell-extension-move-clock, gnome-shell-extension-dashtodock, gnome-shell-extension-refreshwifi
Description: Most useful extensions for Gnome Shell (metapackage)
 This package depends/recommends most useful extensions for Gnome Shell and 
 enables some extensions by default (after lots usability tests in 
 educational and enterprise desktops).
 - Depends on gnome-shell-extension-taskbar, gnome-shell-extension-top-icons-plus,
  gnome-shell-extension-weather, gnome-shell-extensions.
 - Recommends gnome-shell-extension-suspend-button, gnome-shell-extensions-gpaste
 - Suggests gnome-shell-extension-move-clock, gnome-shell-extension-dashtodock,
   gnome-shell-extension-refreshwifi.
 Baltix GNU/Linux GNOME desktop uses these extensions by default, other 
 Debian/Ubuntu based operating systems users also can improve user experience 
 by installing this metapackage.
